skip not-present ACPI devices

Xen and older Qemu expose a boatload (253) ACPI devices to the guest that are not present;
these show up in sysfs but there's nothing meaningful one can do with them.

This patch will have udev skip these devices to save the 100ms+ boot time


--- systemd-233/src/libsystemd/sd-device/device-enumerator.c.org	2017-05-07 02:08:28.775426820 +0000
+++ systemd-233/src/libsystemd/sd-device/device-enumerator.c	2017-05-07 02:12:58.467048034 +0000
